commit.message:
getuto: don't try to speak to smartcards (disable scdaemon)

Disable scdaemon via gpg-agent.conf.

This was really a pain to debug, as gpg would report:
```
gpg: DBG: chan_8 -> KS_GET --ldap -- 0x...
gpg: DBG: chan_8 <- ERR ... No keyserver available <Dirmngr>
gpg: no default secret key: No public key
```

Only with the following could we actually get the useful debugging info:
```
GNUPGHOME=/etc/portage/gnupg gpg --debug-level guru --command-fd 0 \
	--no-permission-warning --yes --no-tty \
	--passphrase-file=/etc/portage/gnupg/pass --pinentry-mode loopback \
	--lsign-key EF9538C9E8E64311A52CDEDFA13D0EF1914E7A72
```

It turns out that it was trying to speak to a smartcard:
```
gpg: DBG: chan_6 -> KEYINFO ...
gpg: DBG: chan_6 <- ERR ... Not found <GPG Agent>
gpg: DBG: get_keygrip for public key
gpg: DBG: keygrip= ...
gpg: DBG: chan_6 -> KEYINFO ...
gpg: DBG: chan_6 <- ERR .... Not found <GPG Agent>
gpg: DBG: chan_6 -> SCD SERIALNO
gpg: DBG: chan_6 <- S SERIALNO ...
```

Thanks to d0nk` for engaging in an extended debugging session on IRC.

Signed-off-by: Sam James <sam@gentoo.org>

commit.message:
Enable bash -x if GETUTO_DEBUG is set

Support enabling verbose bash output if GETUTO_DEBUG is set. Due
getuto often being called via portage it is not trivial to get debug
output. Especially since setting

PORTAGE_TRUST_HELPER="bash -x /usr/bin/getuto"

fails with

!!! Portage trust helper bash -x /usr/bin/getuto for binary packages not found
!!! Continuing, but did you install app-portage/getuto?

Signed-off-by: Florian Schmaus <flow@gentoo.org>
Closes: https://github.com/projg2/getuto/pull/11
Signed-off-by: Sam James <sam@gentoo.org>

commit.message:
getuto: move set -e to after sourcing gentoo-functions

Workaround for failure w/ set -e because of the tput call in gentoo-functions. This
needs to be fixed in gentoo-functions properly too (and in fact it already has been
in git, just not in the last release, 0.19), but we should avoid being fragile
to external issues anyway.

Closes: https://github.com/projg2/getuto/issues/8
Signed-off-by: Sam James <sam@gentoo.org>
